OL,3,CChanging time of day for asthma
OL,4,Cmedication 'could help symptoms'
OL,6,FA mid-afternoon puff of a preventer
OL,7,Finhaler could be the best way for a
OL,8,Fperson with asthma to keep their
OL,9,Fsymptoms under control, according to a
OL,10,Fnew study.
OL,12,FAcademics, led by experts from the
OL,13,FUniversity of Manchester, found that
OL,14,Fif a person with asthma takes their
OL,15,Fbrown inhaler between 3pm and 4pm they
OL,16,Fmay see symptoms improve.
