OL,3,CChanging time of day for asthma
OL,4,Cmedication 'could help symptoms'
OL,6,F"This study shows that aligning the
OL,7,Ftiming of beclomethasone ` 'the brown
OL,8,Finhaler', a commonly taken asthma
OL,9,Ftreatment ` with the body clock could
OL,10,Fhave significant impacts on treatment
OL,11,Foutcomes.
OL,13,F"And this occurred without any of the
OL,14,Fassociated adverse effects or costs of
OL,15,Ftaking higher doses of steroids.
OL,17,F"Our findings warrant further
OL,18,Fvalidation in a larger clinical trial
OL,19,Fto establish clinical feasibility in a
OL,20,Freal-life setting and to evaluate the
OL,21,Fhealth and economic impacts."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUyD@AOU}D@]O]
