OL,3,CChanging time of day for asthma
OL,4,Cmedication 'could help symptoms'
OL,6,FCommenting on the study, Dr Erika
OL,7,FKennington, head of research and
OL,8,Finnovation at Asthma and Lung UK,
OL,9,Fsaid: "A brilliantly simple piece of
OL,10,Frespiratory research shows that
OL,11,Faltering the time of day you take your
OL,12,Fpreventer inhaler dose may have a huge
OL,13,Fimpact on your medication's
OL,14,Feffectiveness.
OL,16,F"It's incredible to think that
OL,17,Fsomething so easy as switching the
OL,18,Ftiming of your inhaler dose to the
OL,19,Fafternoon, has the potential to
OL,20,Fimprove your symptoms and ultimately
OL,21,Fcould save your life.
OL,26,@qD@GOUxD@AOU
